-- India Pension Fund Will Not Invest in Stocks, Commissioner Chatterjee Says
-- B y   A n o o p   A g r a w a l
-- 2010-10-22T15:42:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/india-pension-fund-will-not-invest-in-stocks-commissioner-chatterjee-says.html
India’s Employees’ Provident Fund
Organisation will not invest in equities in the ‘near future,’
Central Provident Fund Commissioner Samirendra Chatterjee told
reporters in Mumbai today.  The pension fund manages 3.25 trillion rupees at present
and plans to pay at least 8.5 percent interest in the year
ending March 31, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
